{"expireTime":9007200818806242000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-b22ffe6782cebe2cf6f2056e5d1e42d1-gatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-autolink-headers-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"There is an unmatched clarity to creating art within limitation. ","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":66,"offset":66},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":66,"offset":66},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"In my Wesleyan junior fall, I seized such an opportunity. I directed the very play that thrust me into \nthe realm of theater. ","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":68},"end":{"line":5,"column":23,"offset":194},"indent":[1]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":68},"end":{"line":5,"column":23,"offset":194},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":null,"url":"../images/stainedglass.jpg","alt":"Stained glass.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":196},"end":{"line":7,"column":46,"offset":241},"indent":[]},"value":"<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 850px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/40850ad4b37c360a68a72fabbf7147af/0e720/stainedglass.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.85057471264368%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Stained glass.\"\n        title=\"Stained glass.\"\n        src=\"/static/40850ad4b37c360a68a72fabbf7147af/4fcb7/stainedglass.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/40850ad4b37c360a68a72fabbf7147af/09a7d/stainedglass.jpg 213w,\n/static/40850ad4b37c360a68a72fabbf7147af/28bbc/stainedglass.jpg 425w,\n/static/40850ad4b37c360a68a72fabbf7147af/4fcb7/stainedglass.jpg 850w,\n/static/40850ad4b37c360a68a72fabbf7147af/0e720/stainedglass.jpg 870w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 850px) 100vw, 850px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>"}],"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1,"offset":196},"end":{"line":7,"column":46,"offset":241},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ayad Akhatar's \"Disgraced\" was first presented to me as an opportunity to leverage \nmy identity as a young Desi male and perform several times as Hussein Malik / Abe Jensen, whose experience mirrors my own (to an extent, thankfully). The Readers' Theater of Connecticut had reached out to Wesleyan's Muslim Chaplain and to its Theater Dept. querying for someone who fit the description (a rare moment where, for a man of color, 'fit the description' was something undeniably positive).","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":243},"end":{"line":10,"column":402,"offset":728},"indent":[1]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1,"offset":243},"end":{"line":10,"column":402,"offset":728},"indent":[1]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"At that time, I ached to act and probably would have accepted any role. I remember my freshman self dashing to the Office of Religious Life to meet with directors Anne Cassady and Richard Kamins, clearing my throat to try out for the part. No knowledge or preparation of the play beforehand, I was essentially cast because I was one of the first and only people to have responded to their casting call.","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":730},"end":{"line":12,"column":403,"offset":1132},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":1,"offset":730},"end":{"line":12,"column":403,"offset":1132},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fast forward to two years later; I was handing out sides for the parts I had grown to know almost as people in their own right. In my head, 'Isaac', 'Jory', 'Abe', 'Emily', and especially 'Amir' were real, and spoke to me, and each of them was the type of person who would be indignant if I botched their casting. ","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":1134},"end":{"line":14,"column":315,"offset":1448},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":1,"offset":1134},"end":{"line":14,"column":315,"offset":1448},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'd like to say I didn't! I wouldn't know, for as I was steeped in weeks of rehearsal, the students in front of me grew into their roles so well that, as far as I was concerned, they ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1450},"end":{"line":16,"column":184,"offset":1633},"indent":[]}},{"type":"emphasis","children":[{"type":"text","value":"were","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":185,"offset":1634},"end":{"line":16,"column":189,"offset":1638},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":184,"offset":1633},"end":{"line":16,"column":190,"offset":1639},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" the characters, just as I had become 'Abe' when I embodied him years prior. ","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":190,"offset":1639},"end":{"line":16,"column":267,"offset":1716},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":1,"offset":1450},"end":{"line":16,"column":267,"offset":1716},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":null,"url":"../images/d3.JPG","alt":"Photograph by Elijah Comas.","position":{"start":{"line":24,"column":1,"offset":1724},"end":{"line":24,"column":49,"offset":1772},"indent":[]},"value":"<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  